Backend project for a web application - Subscription Management System
// This project is a backend service for a subscription management system that allows users to manage their subscriptions,
// This project is designed to handle the backend logic, database interactions, security, automated workflows and API endpoints for the web application.


// The project structure is organized to separate concerns, making it easier to maintain and scale.
// Tech Stack:
// - Node.js: JavaScript runtime for building the backend service.
// - Express.js: Web framework for building APIs.
// - MongoDB: NoSQL database for storing user and subscription data.
// - Mongoose: ODM for MongoDB to interact with the database.
// - JWT: JSON Web Token for authentication and authorization.
// - Upstash: Serverless database for email reminders and workflows.
// - Arcjet: Advanced rate limiting and bot protection for securing the application.

// Features:
// Advanced Rate Limiting and Bot Protection: with Arcjet that helps secure the whole application.
// Database Modeling: Models and relationship using Mongoose & MongoDB.
// JWT Authentication: User CRUD operations and subscription management.
// Global Error Handling: Input validation annd middleare integreation.
// Logging Mechanism: For better debugging and monitoring.
// Email Reminders: Automating smart email reminders with workflows using Upstash.

